T1  - Management in Perspective Discussion: A Reporting System for PERT
AU  - Zelnick, Joel
Y1  - 1963/03/01
PY  - 1963
DA  - 1963/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254879
DO  - 10.5465/254879
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 79
EP  - 80
VL  - 6
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article focuses on exception reporting as an approach to project evaluation and review technique. The author presents an overview of the principles of exception reporting. A discussion is presented about the application of exception reporting in an organization and benefits of exception reporting for the efficiency of managerial efficiency and organizational effectiveness. Details related to the development of an exception reporting program in an organization and methods used to minimize paperwork are presented.
