TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Assignment Problem: Managing a Management Course
AU  - Golembiewski, Robert T.
Y1  - 1963/03/01
PY  - 1963
DA  - 1963/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254874
DO  - 10.5465/254874
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 18
EP  - 35
VL  - 6
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses a study which examines the sociological and psychological aspects of the assignment problem- the placement of individuals in condition which inspire rather than curb effort- by applying it in classroom situations. A discussion is presented about psychological aspects of the work environment and how organizational effectiveness is affected by the assignment problem. The author presents descriptions of tools of measurement, tests of predictions, and implications for the management of cooperative effort.
