TY  - JOUR
T1  - Is There an Organizational Multiplier?
AU  - Hicks, Herbert G.
AU  - Graves, Benjamin B.
Y1  - 1963/03/01
PY  - 1963
DA  - 1963/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254878
DO  - 10.5465/254878
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 70
EP  - 78
VL  - 6
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents information on a study on the impact of organizational multiplier, which stems from the natural tendency among individuals within organizations to try to act in ways which maximize their own welfare. A discussion is presented about the effects of the multiplier on the overall effectiveness of the organization. An overview of the tenet of the multiplier principle is presented, along with illustrations of the workings of the multipliers and mathematical expression of the multiplier.
AB  - The article presents information on a study on the impact of organizational multiplier, which stems from the natural tendency among individuals within organizations to try to act in ways which maximize their own welfare. A discussion is presented about the effects of the multiplier on the overall effectiveness of the organization. An overview of the tenet of the multiplier principle is presented, along with illustrations of the workings of the multipliers and mathematical expression of the multiplier.
