TY  - JOUR
T1  - Management Theory: Functional and Evolutionary
AU  - Suojanen, Waino W.
Y1  - 1963/03/01
PY  - 1963
DA  - 1963/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254873
DO  - 10.5465/254873
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 7
EP  - 17
VL  - 6
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - It is the central thesis of this paper that the enterprise can usefully be described as a man-directed, dynamic network of processes and facilitating systems, and that a useful model of the administrator's job logically follows from this description. We shall first contrast the concepts of ?process? and ?system? and then integrate these concepts with certain other constructs toward building (a) a model of the enterprise and (b) a model of the administrator's job.
AB  - It is the central thesis of this paper that the enterprise can usefully be described as a man-directed, dynamic network of processes and facilitating systems, and that a useful model of the administrator's job logically follows from this description. We shall first contrast the concepts of ?process? and ?system? and then integrate these concepts with certain other constructs toward building (a) a model of the enterprise and (b) a model of the administrator's job.
