TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Application of Queuing Theory to the Span of Control
AU  - Hill, Lawrence S.
Y1  - 1963/03/01
PY  - 1963
DA  - 1963/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254877
DO  - 10.5465/254877
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 58
EP  - 69
VL  - 6
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents information on a study which applied queuing theory to investigate the span of control problem. The author focuses on the issue of ratio of supervisors to subordinates and how many employees a manager can efficiently direct. A discussion is presented about the principle of span of control and properties of waiting line theory. Details related to the application of queuing theory to line manufacturing supervision are presented. The author provides an economic model of queuing theory applied in a military setting.
